<br />
I know there are other big commercial uses but blizzard patching is likely the most widely used torrent system that is completely transparent to the user.(as in it uses the protocol but the user does not have to know a thing about torrent clients.)<br />
<br />
I think the most important thing to get torrents into more usage for legal reasons is for more self containment,   Today we have the problem still that lots of legal torrent activity still needs a special client and that is too complex for the average user.
