				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Stigma Around Bittorrent
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1808977">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							BSD is dead.<br />
<br />
Once you become more focused on purity than stability or administrative capability, you've lost.  And once you look at your competitor (Linux) as the enemy, and immediately decide that everything they do is wrong, you've lost.<br />
<br />
In 2012 their servers were hacked, using a problem found and fixed in Linux in 2007.<br />
<br />
The BSD projects refuse to use or implement Virtualization, which makes their support costs pretty incredible, and guarantees that everyone everywhere will be running some form of Linux (being generous here to include ESXi as Linux.  While it isn't Linux, to run it you end up with SuSe virtuals or Windows servers) or Windows, and if you go that far, why would you want to have something that doesn't deal well with virtualization?
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
