				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Stigma Around Bittorrent
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1809069">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				<div class="bbcode_postedby">
					<img src="images/misc/quote_icon.png" alt="Quote" /> Originally Posted by <strong>MI Redeux</strong>
					<a href="showthread.php?s=806f2e17e5b773de385d7e932a795e2b&amp;p=1809033#post1809033" rel="nofollow"><img class="inlineimg" src="images/buttons/viewpost-right.png" alt="View Post" /></a>
				</div>
				<div class="message">I definitely agree and I hate how most things target them and end up sacrificing a lot of utility along the way, with Firefox and iWorks being a great example of sabotaging themselves chasing that demographic. Deluge is really stupid easy though and available everywhere. It has a different ranking algorithm used but does not demand any interaction by the user unless they want to tweak them. It's the best client by far IMO without manipulating libtorrent directly.</div>
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>The issue is the average user at least in the US will tell you &quot;I do not have time to learn about this stuff.&quot;   Or &quot;I do no care to know this computer geek bullshit,  Just make it work&quot;.   Sadly at least here in the US the typical citizen does not care to know,  They want their tech to be light switch simple(I was going to say microwave oven but I have seen people have trouble with those too).   But hey this is why Apple is thriving,  They make technology so simple a dog could figure it out.  While making sure its near impossible or not existing at all when it comes to finding advanced settings.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
