			<div class="postrow has_after_content">
				
				
				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Stigma Around Bittorrent
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1809938">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							I think BT is useful for the personal level - folder sharing and syncing is the newest hotness, right? - as well as large file sharing. Honestly, I think we're going to see the death of the RIAA/MPAA, or at least their dimishment &amp; departure into the ... west? The EU is on the road to copyright reform and file sharing, the developing portions of the world (Asia, Africa, ME, Eastern Europe) don't care, and the western developed world is full of tech-savvy people who know how to operate behind a proxy or a VPN.<br />
<br />
Plus, with surveillance being such a hot topic, encryption and VPN usage is increasing, anyway, which also reduces any concerns about &quot;illegality&quot; of BT.<br />
<br />
In the end, the stigma will wash away. Other methods for sharing might come to fruition, but they'll probably be some of the same idea - jump in the pool, ask for a file, get parts from many people.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<div class="after_content">
				
                                       
                                 
				
		        		<blockquote class="signature restore"><div class="signaturecontainer"><i><font size="1">FABRICATI DIEM, PVNC</font></i><br />
